    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-11-06T03:37:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-11-06T03:37:00-05:00" n="682"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d682">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Lot 55D128: Black Book, Tab 56: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Commander in Chief, Far East</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ridgway</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Joint Chiefs of
                            Staff</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret   priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-11-06T17:37:00+09:00">6
                            November 1951—5:37 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>C–56713. For info, <gloss target="#t_CINCUNC1">CINCUNC</gloss> Adv HNC 426.</p>
                <p>“Sub-delegation reports as follows on meeting this date: Communists presented
                    long prepared statement rejecting our proposal of yesterday on basis agenda item
                    2 must be finally solved before going to other items.</p>
                <p>“Communists now want determine present line of contact and make that line the
                    final military line of demarcation of the demilitarized zone regardless of the
                    time the military armistice is eventually signed or the actual location of the
                    line of contact at that time. This concept is in complete disagreement with what
                    they have previously said and with our own views.</p>
                <p>“We pointed out that terms of armistice dependent on conditions at time of
                    signing of armistice and that tentative agreement reached on each item might be
                    modified if conditions on which tentative agreement was based changed
                    significantly.</p>
                <p>“No indications their future action.</p>
                <p>“We will continue press for agreement on our proposal outlined in HNC 423.<note
                        n="1" xml:id="d682fn1">Dated November 4, <ref target="#pg_1087">p.
                            1087</ref>.</note> We do not intend agree to permanently fixing
                    demilitarized zone until armistice is signed.</p>
                <p>“Meet tomorrow 1100. Signed Joy.”</p>
            </div>
